  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "From discord: \"Hey everyone, I have Nethermind installed via the Ubuntu PPA and I have noticed that whenever I update it, the JWT secret which is located at \"/var/lib/nethermind/keystore/jwt.hex\" gets deleted. Then when I start Nethermind again, it generates a new JWT secret meaning that the beacon node does not communicate with Nethermind anymore as they are different. Then I have to stop Nethermind and copy the JWT secret back over again and start it up. This happens every time so now I copy the JWT secret over before I start Nethermind, but I also wanted to raise this here as it doesn't seem like it is expected behaviour.\"\r\n",
